2026-05-04 | Rotate Image by 90 Degrees Clockwise

Question
Modify matrix to its rotated form.
	Key Insight
Rotation can be done in 2 steps:
1.	Transpose the matrix  
		swap (i,j) ↔ (j,i)  
2.	Reverse each row  
Why this works:
		transpose flips across diagonal  
		row reverse gives rotation  
	Approach
1.	Transpose matrix:
		for i:
			for j > i:
				swap(mat[i][j], mat[j][i])  
2.	Reverse each row  
	Time Complexity
	O(n²)
	Space Complexity
	O(1)
	Solution
class Solution {
public:
    void rotate(vector<vector<int>>& matrix) {
        int n = matrix.size();
        // Step 1: Transpose
        for(int i = 0; i < n; i++){
            for(int j = i+1; j < n; j++){
                swap(matrix[i][j], matrix[j][i]);
            }
        }
        // Step 2: Reverse each row
        for(int i = 0; i < n; i++){
            reverse(matrix[i].begin(), matrix[i].end());
        }
    }
};
	Key Insight
Instead of rotating layer by layer:
		use mathematical transformation  
Transpose + Reverse:
		simplifies the problem cleanly and efficiently  
This is the standard optimal in-place solution.
